    "words_per_page": "mean 894, coefficient of variation 2.0% across 30 years (977 in 1994, 898 in 2023)",
    "verdict": "The two independently-sourced series agree closely on level and trend (r=0.9945) and the implied words-per-page ratio is near-constant, which is what you expect if both are measuring the same underlying stock. Year-over-year increments do NOT correlate (r=0.05): annual changes are small relative to the lumpiness of page counts and reissue timing, so neither series is reliable for single-year deltas. Pages grow slightly faster than words (2.02% vs 1.72% CAGR), consistent with typesetting/layout drift."
